      "content": "that's a good start, but it feels a bit too \"safe\" for a high-level sociology paper. i want to really hammer home why the idea of \"meritocracy\" is actually just a way to justify the current system and keep things unfair. could you add a section that critiques the meritocracy argument and shows how it's basically used to ignore systemic racism? like, make it clear why that viewpoint is problematic from a sociological perspective.",
